Content:: S. M. M. Muszhaaraff (Tamil: எஸ். எம். எம். முஷாரப்; Sinhala: එස්. එම්. එම්. මුෂාරෆ්; (born 10 June 1983) is a Sri Lankan politician and member of Parliament for Digamadulla District.[1][2][3] Muszhaaraff was born on 10 June 1983.[4] He is the son of Meeralebbe Safiul Muthunabeen & Meerashahibu Katheeja Beevi.[5] Muszhaaraff worked as a TV presenter and producer. He has won several State Awards for his shows.[6]  This article about a politician from Eastern Province, Sri Lanka is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.
